    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-05-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-05-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="8"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d8">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to Prime
                        Minister <persName type="to">Churchill</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d8fn1">Sent to the United States Naval Attaché London, via
                        Navy channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-31">31 May
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Number 546. Personal and top secret. From the President for the <gloss
                        target="#t_FormerNavalPerson1">Former Naval Person</gloss>.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>I should like very much to accept Dr. Churchill’s advice to make a sea voyage in
                    your direction and I hope to do so at a later date. Conditions here will not
                    permit it shortly after <gloss target="#t_D141">D plus 14</gloss> as suggested
                    by you.</p>
                <pb facs="0061" n="7" xml:id="pg_7"/>
                <p>Developments of the <gloss target="#t_Overlord1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Overlord</hi>
                    </gloss> campaign should point with some accuracy to the time when a meeting of
                    the Combined Staff is necessary. I think we had best await developments of
                        <gloss target="#t_Overlord1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Overlord</hi>
                    </gloss> before making a decision as to the next full Staff meeting.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
